-- India's IDFC Alternatives raises $902 mln for second infra fund
-- By Indulal PM
-- Thu Oct 09, 2014 05:56AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, Oct 9 (Reuters) - IDFC Alternatives Ltd, the private equity arm of India's IDFC Ltd <IDFC.NS>, said on Thursday it had raised 55 billion rupees ($902.4 million) for its second fund investing in infrastructure assets in the country.

The fund includes a commitment of about $90 million from IDFC, while about $810 million would come from outside investors, including from North America, Europe and the Middle East, IDFC said in a statement.